## §1 — Layer rules (mechanically enforced)

Your project's layer rules are encoded in `.cadence/cadence.yaml`
under `boundaries:`. The boundary checker (`tool/check_boundaries.py`)
enforces them on every `scripts/verify` run.

Default boundaries assumed by Cadence:

- `features/**` may NOT import `data/sources/**` or `data/repositories/**`
- `data/sources/**` may NOT import `features/**` or `app/**`
- `app/**` may NOT import `features/**` (cycle avoidance)
- Models live under `domain/models/**` (NEVER `data/models/**`)

Customize for your project in `cadence.yaml`.

## §2 — Controller shape

Document the project's chosen state-management pattern and which
