## §3 — Narrow function-typed providers

Feature code reads narrow providers, not repositories directly. See
ADR-NNNN.

## §4 — Mutation pattern

Optimistic-then-write (default per ADR-NNNN), with documented exceptions.

## §5 — Error surface

Three levels: whole-screen `AsyncError`, per-action state field,
per-row map. See ADR-NNNN.

## §6 — UI async invocation

Wrap fire-and-forget async calls per the project's stack convention
(`unawaited()` for Dart, `void` cast for TS, etc.).

## §7 — Test requirements

Per ADR-NNNN: happy + edge + sequence + error + write log.

## §8 — Style

Per the project's lint config in `cadence.yaml` `commands.lint`.

